l%20be%20the%20largest%20vessel%20of%20its%20kind.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20ship's%20large%20size%20isn't%20the%20only%20detail%20that%20sets%20it%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20other%20amphibious%20assault%20ships%20have%20only%20been%20able%20to%20carry%20helicopters%20and%20vertical%2Fshort%20takeoff%20and%20landing%20aircraft%2C%20the%20Sichuan%20is%20equipped%20with%20a%20carrier-style%20catapult%20system%20and%20arresting%20gear%20that%20allows%20it%20to%20launch%20heavier%20fixed-wing%20aircraft%2C%20the%20Chinese%20navy%20said.%20Even%20with%20the%20unveiling%2C%20mystery%20still%20shrouds%20what%20is%20essentially%20a%20light%20aircraft%20carrier%20and%20China's%20ambitions%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWorld's%20largest%20amphibious%20assault%20ship%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224455%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22China's%20first%20Type%20076%20new-generation%20amphibious%20assault%20ship%2C%20the%20Sichuan%2C%20is%20docked%20at%20Hudong-Zhonghua%20Shipbuilding.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F676ef193a3e82c791204902d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222970%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Type%20076%20amphibious%20assault%20ship%20is%20much%20longer%20and%20larger%20than%20its%20predecessor%2C%20the%20Yushen-class%20Type%20075.%3Cp%3EPu%20Haiyang%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EConstruction%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-shipbuilding-power-players-making-warships-at-a-rapid-pace-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20next-generation%20assault%20ship%3C%2Fa%3E%20began%20in%20early%202024%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Pentagon's%20annual%20congressional%20report%20on%20China's%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20displacement%20of%2040%2C000%20tons%2C%20satellite%20images%20show%20the%20Sichuan%20measures%20more%20than%20850%20feet%20long%20and%20about%20170%20feet%20wide%2C%20making%20it%20considerably%20larger%20than%20its%20Chinese%20predecessor%2C%20the%20Type%20075%2C%20but%20smaller%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-new-aircraft-carrier-more-to-learn-to-match-us-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Fujian%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army's%20newest%20and%20largest%20aircraft%20carrier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Type%20076%20is%20also%20much%20larger%20than%20Japan's%20Izumo-class%20helicopter%20carriers.%20While%20the%20Sichuan%20is%20about%20as%20long%20as%20the%20US%20Navy's%20America-class%20LHAs%20with%20a%20similar%20displacement%2C%20it%20is%20more%20than%2060%20feet%20wider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20warship's%20larger%20size%20and%20deck%20space%20allow%20it%20to%20accommodate%20both%20fixed-wing%20aircraft%20and%20helicopters%2C%20with%20additional%20storage%20capacity%20for%20more%20personnel%20and%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EElectromagnetic%20catapult%20system%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20satellite%20image%20showing%20China's%20new%20amphibious%20assault%20ship%20being%20built%20in%20a%20shipyard.%20There%20is%20a%20text%20overlay%20showing%20the%20length%20of%20the%20trench%20for%20launching%20aircraft.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bf9b335da406397bf6a813%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20satellite%20image%20shows%20the%20Type%20076's%20top%20deck.%3Cp%3ECSIS%2FChina%20Power%2FCNES%202024%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20traditional%20light%20aircraft%20carriers%2C%20the%20Sichuan%20is%20equipped%20with%20a%20catapult%20system%20and%20arresting%20gear%20for%20the%20launch%20and%20recovery%20of%20fixed-wing%20aircraft%20%E2%80%94%20an%20operative%20capability%20typically%20reserved%20for%20aircraft%20carriers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20something%20that%20we've%20seen%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20Matthew%20Funaiole%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20with%20the%20China%20Power%20Project%20at%20CSIS%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-unusual-assault-ship-was-rapidly-built-purpose-a-mystery-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20BI%20previously%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BNo%20other%20country%20has%20an%20LHA%20that%20has%20a%20catapult%20system%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20electromagnetic%20aircraft%20launch%20system%20(EMALS)%20is%20likely%20similar%20in%20design%20to%20the%20catapult%20aboard%20the%20US%20Navy's%20advanced%20Ford-class%20supercarriers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20warship%20in%20operational%20service%20that%20employs%20EMALS%20is%20the%20US%20Navy%20carrier%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford.%20China's%20third%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20the%20Fujian%2C%20which%20has%20been%20undergoing%20shake-down%20trials%20at%20sea%2C%20also%20features%20three%20EMALS-style%20catapults%2C%20but%20the%20Sichuan's%20catapult%20trench%2C%20which%20is%20over%20425%20feet%20long%2C%20is%20significantly%20longer%20by%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20Chinese%20carriers%20had%20ski-jump-style%20ramps%20for%20launching%20aircraft%20without%20catapults%2C%20leaping%20past%20steam-power%20catapult%20technology%20to%20pursue%20the%20more%20advanced%20electromagnetic%20launch%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOperating%20for%20a%20little%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20China's%20relatively%20young%20carrier%20force%20could%20still%20face%20a%26quot%3Bsteep%20learning%20curve%26quot%3B%20in%20employing%20modern%20catapult%20technology%2C%20retired%20Adm.%20Raymond%20Spicer%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20publisher%20at%20the%20US%20Naval%20Institute%2C%20previously%20told%20BI.%20But%20the%20installation%20of%20the%20technology%20aboard%20the%20Type%20076%20could%20indicate%20China's%20confidence%20in%20the%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPotential%20future%20'drone%20carrier'%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224455%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20wide%20flight%20deck%20of%20the%20Chinese%20amphibious%20assault%20ship%2C%20the%20Sichuan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F676ef1939de00e389eb39609%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222970%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Sichuan%20has%20a%20full-length%20launch%20deck%20featuring%20an%20electromagnetic%20catapult%20system%2C%20likely%20for%20launching%20unmanned%20aerial%20vehicles.%3Cp%3EPu%20Haiyang%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20navy%20has%20yet%20to%20confirm%20what%20kind%20of%20air%20wing%20will%20operate%20aboard%20the%20Sichuan%2C%20but%20it%20could%20have%20a%20future%20role%20as%20a%20massive%20drone%20carrier%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fchinas-massive-next-generation-amphibious-assault-ship-takes-shape%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vessel's%20catapult%2C%20wider%20flight%20deck%2C%20and%20unobstructed%20runway%20make%20it%20highly%20capable%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-navy-likely-built-world-first-drone-carrier-report-taiwan-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elarge-scale%20drone%20operations%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20China%20expands%20its%20arsenal%20of%20UAVs%2C%20like%20the%20Hongdu%20GJ-11%20stealth%20combat%20drone%2C%20Guizhou%20WZ-7%20reconnaissance%20drone%2C%20and%20the%20CASC%20CH-4B%20Rainbow%20strike%20UCAV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E'A%20substantial%20step%20forward'%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227936%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Plumes%20of%20colorful%20smoke%20surround%20the%20Sichuan%20during%20the%20amphibious%20assault%20ship's%20launching%20ceremony%20in%20China.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F676ef193a3e82c791204902e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224672%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPlumes%2