%20alt%3D%5C%22Ivan%20Scherman%2C%20stock%20trader%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6765e0f063b028ed846a01f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222589%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EIvan%20Scherman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EStock%20market%20volatility%20may%20be%20elevated%20as%20we%20enter%20the%20first%20year%20after%20an%20election.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIvan%20Scherman%2C%20a%20hedge%20fund%20manager%2C%20uses%20mechanical%20trading%20to%20leverage%20market%20volatility.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20recommended%20strategy%20involves%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20and%20VIX%20divergence%2C%20with%20a%2075.3%25%20win%20ratio%20from%20backtests.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20year%20after%20an%20election%20tends%20to%20bring%20elevated%20volatility%20for%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-trading-strategy-quant-fund-manager-competition-champion-sp500-return-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIvan%20Scherman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fchart-patterns-technical-analysts-used-by-buy-stocks-analysis-market-2020-5-1029263411%23%3A~%3Atext%3DVisit%2520Business%2520Insider%2527s%2520homepage%2520for%2520more%2520stories.%26amp%3Btext%3DTechnical%2520analysts%2520attempt%2520to%2520take%2Cdriven%2520by%2520fear%2520and%2520greed.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echartered%20market%20technician%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20hedge%20fund%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20the%20incoming%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-trump-trade-stock-market-bonds-commodities-tariffs-fed-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20administration%3C%2Fa%3E%20implements%20more%20extreme%20policy%20changes%2C%20that%20may%20kick%20that%20volatility%20up%20a%20notch.%20But%20it's%20not%20a%20bad%20thing%20if%20you're%20a%20trader%20because%20you%20can%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20peaks%20and%20valleys%2C%20said%20Scherman%2C%20who%20won%20the%202023%20World%20Cup%20Trading%20Championship%20for%20futures%20with%20a%20491.4%25%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20something%20you%20have%20to%20fear%2C%26quot%3B%20Scherman%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20you%20need%20to%20wait%20for%20the%20proper%20time%20in%20order%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20conditions%20that%20the%20volatility%20is%20going%20to%20give%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20quant%20fund%20manager%2C%20he%20has%20backtested%20thousands%20of%20models%20before%20putting%20hundreds%20of%20them%20to%20work%20while%20he%20monitors%20their%20progress.%20Using%20a%20machine%20to%20make%20trades%20means%20he%20can%20diversify%20bets%20across%20everything%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20coffee%20and%20even%20soybeans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20perhaps%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20advantages%20of%20a%20mechanical%20approach%20is%20that%20it%20allows%20him%20to%20set%20his%20emotions%20aside%3A%20a%20shift%20that%20every%20successful%20trader%20eventually%20realizes%20is%20key%20to%20survival%20because%20it%20prevents%20rash%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20not%20everyone%20has%20the%20ability%20to%20backtest%20and%20build%20quant%20models%2C%20there%20are%20mechanical%20trades%20that%20can%20be%20executed%20manually.%20In%20a%20volatile%20market%2C%20Scherman%20likes%20a%20pattern%20that%20spots%20a%20divergence%20between%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fvix%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECBOE%20Volatility%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%20(VIX)%2C%20which%20is%20used%20to%20measure%20expected%20volatility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pattern%2C%20which%20has%20been%20backtested%20from%201957%20to%20date%2C%20showed%20the%20strategy%20had%20a%20win%20ratio%20of%2075.3%25%20and%20a%20profit%20factor%20of%203.16%2C%20which%20means%20for%20every%20dollar%20you%20lose%2C%20you%20can%20make%20%243.16%2C%20Scherman%20noted.%20Despite%20its%20long%20track%20record%20of%20success%2C%20past%20behavior%20does%20not%20guarantee%20future%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20no%20guarantee%20that%20this%20is%20going%20to%20keep%20happening%20in%20the%20future%2C%20of%20course%2C%26quot%3B%20Scherman%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20think%20it's%20a%20very%20stable%20pattern%20because%20it%20responds%20to%20one%20of%20the%20internals%20of%20the%20market%2C%20which%20is%20the%20put-buying%20that%20institutions%20use%20in%20order%20to%20hedge%20their%20positions.%20If%20they%20are%20not%20buying%20puts%2C%20they're%20not%20hedging%20their%20positions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20this%20strategy%20from%202006%20to%202018%2C%20both%20for%20me%20and%20for%20the%20fund%20I%20work%20for.%20I%20personally%20traded%20with%20the%20e-mini%20S%26amp%3BP%20500.%20For%20the%20fund%2C%20I%20traded%20it%20by%20using%20SPY%20and%20SPXL.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScherman%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20traded%20this%20pattern%20both%20for%20his%20personal%20account%20and%20hedge%20fund%20with%20very%20good%20outcomes%20but%20isn't%20authorized%20to%20disclose%20performance%20metrics%20due%20to%20compliance.%20Today%2C%20his%20fund%20trades%20an%20improved%20version%20of%20the%20trade%20that%20can't%20be%20disclosed%20to%20maintain%20competitive%20advantages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%20is%20a%20chart%20that%20shows%20the%20profit%20potential%20of%20repeating%20the%20trade%20over%20time%20pulled%20from%20the%20backtest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221123%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22graph%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6765edb45cddac6581d76de2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22842%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EIvan%20Sherman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a4310afa-8363-451c-867c-104e271d90d4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20mechanical%20trade%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20setup%20requires%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20and%20the%20VIX%20set%20up%20on%20the%20same%20chart.%20The%20notion%20then%20follows%20that%20when%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20experiences%20a%20correction%2C%20signaled%20by%20a%20drop%20in%20price%2C%20the%20VIX%20should%20spike%20in%20correlation%20to%20that%20dip%2C%20as%20a%20likely%20sign%20that%20institutional%20investors%20are%20buying%20puts%20as%20a%20hedge%20against%20the%20correction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20first%20correction%20is%20followed%20by%20a%20second%20dip%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20lower%20low%20than%20the%20first%2C%20the%20VIX%20should%20also%20see%20a%20second%20spike%20in%20correlation.%20However%2C%20the%20VIX%20should%20technically%20see%20a%20higher%20high.%20But%20if%20the%20second%20VIX%20spike%20isn't%20higher%20than%20its%20prior%20spike%2C%20this%20slight%20discrepancy%20is%20what%20Scherman%20calls%20the%20divergence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20pattern%20is%20provoked%20by%20big%20institutions%20that%20don't%20believe%20that%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20in%20a%20steeper%20correction%2C%20so%20they%20won't%20hedge%20by%20buying%20further%20puts%2C%20causing%20a%20more%20muted%20spike%20in%20the%20VIX.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20required%20condition%20is%20that%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500's%20price%20movements%20should%20not%20be%20farther%20out%20than%20two%20standard%20deviations%20from%20the%2030-day%20moving%20average%2C%20a%20range%20that%20can%20be%20set%20using%20Bollinger%20bands.%20If%20the%20index's%20price%20swings%20fall%20outside%20the%20Bollinger%20band%2C%20in%20this%20instance%20below%20it%2C%20the%20trade%20should%20not%20be%20taken%2C%20Scherman%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20all%20conditions%20are%20met%2C%20the%20trader%20should%20buy%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20at%20the%20close%20of%20the%20stock%20market%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%20is%20a%20chart%20demonstrating%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20in%20correlation%20to%20the%20VIX.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221832%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22CHart%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6769df8ba3e82c7912041d5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22916%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%20and%20VIX%3Cp%3EIvan%20Scherman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d595d1b9-8123-4c95-90ff-3383df04950b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20exit%20strategy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20in%20the%20trade%2C%20there%20are%20two%20exits.%20The%20first%20is%20the%20winning%20one%2C%20which%20happens%20if%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20goes%20above%20the%2030-day%20moving%20average.%20Once%20this%20condition%20is%20met%2C%20the%20trader%20must%20exit%20the%20trade%20at%20the%20close%20of%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20exit%20would%20be%20a%20loss%20and%20would%20be%20executed%20if%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20set%20to%20close%20two%20standard%20deviations%20below%20its%2030-day%20moving%20average%2C%20thus%20outside%20the%20Bollinger%20band.%20Here%2C%20a%20trader%20must%20cut%20their%20losses%20and%20accept%20that%20the%20thesis%20failed.%20Scherman%20noted%20this%20will%20happen%20around%2025%25%20of%20the%20time%20based%20on%20the%20backtest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-trade-stocks-high-win-ratio-and-profit-potential-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735384501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6765e12063b028ed846a020c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-trade-stocks-high-win-ratio-and-profit-potential-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20hedge%20fund%20manager%20b